= La vida interna

Not every month makes history. This one is dues stamps, minutes read and approved, a leaking roof over the mimeograph, and the eternal debate about who left the local unlocked. The Movement's real skeleton is this: the meeting that happens anyway.

- @sostener: Hold the routine together. It is not glamorous. It is the whole thing.
- @easy_discard

@sostener
on-arrival: unity += 1; funds += 1

Quorum was reached, barely. The minutes were approved, with one abstention on principle nobody could explain. The roof got patched. In a police state, continuity is a form of victory, and this month the Party continued.
